gainst running tests, so I should check an existing untracked directory for generated metadata. It looks like we might want to avoid modifying that untracked metadata. Before finalizing everything, I should add a replacement stream to the current test to prevent a NotSerializableException.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_oesyE3f9t30T4lCbYT5rtVh4|fc_074350a35aa1346b0169f80a3395d0819e8f8c0ab738c76a88\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/SoftCachingModuleScriptProviderTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\\n            output.writeObject(provider);\\n        }\", \"newText\": \"        try (ReplacingObjectOutputStream output = new ReplacingObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\\n            output.writeObject(provider);\\n        }\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    private static final class InMemoryModuleSourceProvider\\n            implements ModuleSourceProvider, Serializable {\", \"newText\": \"    private static final class ReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\\n        ReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream bytes) throws IOException {\\n            super(bytes);\\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) {\\n            if (object != null && object.getClass() == Object.class) {\\n                return \\\"serialized-lock\\\";\\n            }\\n            return object;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class InMemoryModuleSourceProvider\\n            implements ModuleSourceProvider, Serializable {\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1770, \"output\": 1126, \"cacheRead\": 44032, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 46928, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\